{
  "local_port": 41994,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "To deposit cash at an ATM, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Locate an ATM that accepts deposits**: Not all ATMs accept deposits, so make sure you find one that does. These are commonly found at bank branches.\n\n2. **Insert your debit card**: Swipe or insert your debit card into the ATM and enter your PIN when prompted.\n\n3. **Select the deposit option**: On the ATM screen, choose the \"Deposit\" option.\n\n4. **Choose the account**: Select the account you want to deposit the money into, such as your checking or savings account.\n\n5. **Prepare your cash**: Make sure your cash is in good condition and remove any staples, paperclips, or rubber bands. Some ATMs may have specific requirements, such as facing the bills in a certain direction or bundling them together.\n\n6. **Insert the cash**: Follow the ATM's instructions to insert the cash into the designated slot. Some ATMs will automatically count the cash, while others may require you to enter the amount manually.\n\n7. **Confirm the amount**: Verify that the amount displayed on the screen is correct. If it's not, you may need to cancel the transaction and start over.\n\n8. **Complete the transaction**: Once you've confirmed the amount, the ATM will process the deposit and return your card. Be sure to take your receipt as proof of the deposit.\n\n9. **Check your account**: It's a good idea to check your account balance online or through your bank's mobile app to ensure the deposit has been credited to your account.\n\nRemember that deposit availability may vary depending on your bank's policies and the time of day you make the deposit.",
